posts.body: Remote Locker Expansion: The remote lockers at the Fort Mill library will be closed Tuesday, May 6, through Thursday, May 8, while we add more lockers. reviews_data.review_text: Very helpful staff. Library is organized and clean.
Love the library. I mostly look on line and reserve the book that our book club reads each month. Easy to pick up, no hassle. Also like using the on line services. Great resources.
Friendly service.   Nice amenities like wifi, printing services.
I love going to this library, and I think its a great place for kids and adults to pick out books, or even come over for some quiet time. I recommend coming if u live in Tega Cay!

One of the best library in York County.
The staff are very nice and helpful.
They keep losing the books I returned to drop-in return. Today they made me physically look for the book THEY lost and tried to make it look like it was my fault.
This is my happy place! Friendly fun staff, warm cozy atmosphere and the perfect place to get lost in a good book! Please visit today!
Clean,  free books,  great area to walk around

I took a long time to write this comment and thought about it several times, but today I had yet another unpleasant experience. I regularly visit this library, and there are always many employees, but some of them are not very available or friendly when dealing with people.

On one occasion, an employee approached the table where I was working with my son and, in an authoritative and unpleasant manner, told me that I had to leave the table and that only my son could stay because he is a teenager. I tried to explain that we were working together and that’s why we were using the table, but she cut me off and left me mid-sentence.

On another occasion, I needed to print a document. They told me the printer was closed, even though it wasn't yet closing time. Apparently, there is an internal rule that only they know about, where they shut down all the technology equipment 15 minutes before closing.

Another day, I sent a document to the printer, and the lady refused to help me because she was busy.

Almost everyone seems to be in a surprising rush to get rid of you, rather than to help.

I love libraries, especially using the one in my community, but this situation is leaving me disillusioned.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
We are sorry to hear that you have not been happy with your experiences here at the library.  
Regarding the employee who asked you to leave the teen area, that space is reserved strictly for teens so that they can have a place all to themselves.  There are not less than five signs in the area indicating this, including one prominently displayed on each table.  Working with a teen is not the same as being a teen.  You were definitely not singled out; we frequently have to ask adults to leave the teen area, many of whom are working with a teen.
Regarding the public computers being unavailable beginning 15 minutes prior to closing each day, that is the case at all YCL libraries and many other public libraries as well.  The reservation software has been set the way for many years by the library’s IT department so that the building can be ready to be vacated at closing time.  There is also a sign indicating this at the library’s entrance.  Regarding the employee who “refused” to help you print a document because she was busy, please ask to speak to the manager if something like that happens.  I am confident that there was just a misunderstanding; it is likely that the employee was in the middle of helping another patron and needed you to wait.  Our staff are incredibly helpful and friendly (yet also busy), which is the overwhelming consensus among our patrons.  We hope that you will keep an open mind and continue to use your local library.

reviews_data.review_text: I’ve enjoyed coming to the library more and more here recently. I’ve gotten a great selection of books for my classroom (toddler age) and books for my personal enjoyment. The staff has always been incredibly kind and helpful. When I had an issue with the lockers they were very quick to help me retrieve my books and very apologetic for it happening. I’d recommend the Baxter location to anyone near it! :)

We live in Fort Mill and keep wanting to love our local library, but it honestly has the least child-friendly staff of any of the libraries we've been to since moving to the area. The Storytime teacher, Ms. Bethany is an absolute gem, but our interactions with everyone else has honestly been anywhere from uncomfortable to down right rude. Today two members of the front desk staff came over to tell me to quiet my kiddo and his little buddy down because they were 'singing the ABC's too loudly'. They were sitting at the kids table in the kids area reading ABC books when they decided to sing - what a wonderful, normal toddler thing to do. Meanwhile Toddler Storytime is going on - it's a kiddo hour at the library. So so sad that our local library is so, so unfriendly.
Nice

This is true about the library being wayyyy too loud! I come quite often and EVERY time it's a high noise level. They also allow people to talk loudly on their phones. Make a sign about no cell phone use. This library also closes whenever they feel like it despite the posted library hours
If you are looking for a quiet place to study or read, Don’t come here. Place is so loud with kids screaming constantly in the afternoon.
Lots of fun books to choose and a whole area for little kids to play one of my favorite libraries. They also have some clubs to join . Although there are no quiet places to study and is pretty loud.
The Fortmill Library is to kid-ish for me . However if you have kids great place.  I like Pineville Library it's kid friendly However more balanced for adults to enjoy

Great selection of children books. Librarians and staff are very pleasant. Lots of fun activities for kids eg chess club, Lego club. Craft handouts. Chess
/checkers/backgammon tables.

This place as a library is a Joke. This should be a reading social house. The amount of noise is ridiculous. Staff loud, people loud and a zoo of loud, whining, or over aroused children. I gave an additional star for the events they offer. This is Fort Mill, SC I know there is some form of funds that can be used to build an addition onto the building for the people who are in the library to study 📖 in a quiet environment.  At least multiple sound proof study rooms. MY GOD!

This library is too loud. This is just ridiculous. The library definitely should regulate how loud people are because guess what? It is a library and so of us came here to get work done and not be in a loud environment.
The loudest library ever. Came here to study but left after 20 minutes.  I won't be returning and wouldn't recommend.
There's a printer for you to print your files and documents for ten cents a copy. Very convenient.

This library has zero activities for younger children. There is no kids' zone or play area--only a space with two toys for the entire library. The head librarian claimed there was no money or space for a kids' zone. Very disappointing--other libraries are far superior.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We are sorry to hear that you were not satisfied with our library on your first visit, but it seems odd to the head librarian to give a public library a 1-star rating based on its limited number of toys.  Regardless, we actually have eight toys available in our children’s area; you must have missed the others.  In addition, we offer many programs/events for young children every month other than August (our planning month).  Last month, for instance, we offered a total of 40 program sessions for children under age five (not to mention the programs for older children); a total of 1,522 patrons attended those 40 programs.  A number of those programs have additional toys available for young children.  Due to the large crowds that often visit our library, we do not have the space available to leave more toys out in the children’s area.  If we had a larger building (which, as the head librarian noted, we do not have the money for), we would certainly expand our children’s area and include more toys.  We hope that you will return and give us a chance to prove that we are in no way a 1-star library.  I can assure you that the service you and your children would receive from our talented and passionate staff would be unsurpassed by other libraries that you have visited.

reviews_data.review_text: Love the place. Librarians here (as in most of the libraries) are polite, knowledgeable and kind. Has a decent collection of books and since this is part of SCLends system, it also provides option of requesting books from all other libraries that are part of this system across SC. They also have a off-hours hold and pickup lockers which is an awesome idea.

This is the loudest library that I have ever experienced in 50 years of living. There is no respect for persons who are engaging in activities that require quiet and focus. If you have to do anything work related or studying for a exams, do not come here.
Fort Mill library is the best !!!
Great  library

Lots of books for children, and things for a 2 year old to play with
Love this place. Quick book hold retrieval and i love that they stay open til 7 on weekdays.
Great customer service and friendly staff.

This is the loudest library I’ve ever been to. The staff is loud, the cell phones are constantly digging, and the place may as well be a romper room with kids running around loudly and uncontrollably. There are few places to escape to that are quiet, and libraries are supposed to be just that. I have a huge medical exam Monday, and had to leave after 30 minutes because I couldn’t concentrate.

FM library, Baxter location, has really been upping their game! Look at that brand new touch screen book hold locker! This will allow people who desire, to pick up their books on hold, before and after library hours!
Employees are always very friendly, and helpful. The new renovations have really cleaned the place up and made it even nicer!
My only complaint, is that I wish they would have a bigger Christian book section. Books are not clearly labeled with stickers that allow readers to see what type of book specifically they might be trying to check out (ie: Christian fiction, etc).
Very well organized. Great for kids. Extremely friendly and helpful staff.
every time， no matter call or stop by, I always get the best service that I have expected.
We love the library 😍
Nice place!
I have been going to this library since I was little and it’s always very organized and is great for kids!!!
I love it here, staff is friendly and it’s a great setup. There are computers that are open to the public and a great selection of books. 5/5 stars ❤️
Wonderful service
This is a very nice library and the staff is so helpful.

Library not having enough  books . Most of the good books long reserved  . Also while returning  some time they miss it . I have to pay for a book which I already  returned  . Not sure how they missed it but next process for fine was more pathetic  . We were asked to pay new book market price  , where as same book were available  new online  40% cheaper  .  We are worried about why people  are not coming to Library  that much but same time should think about  user problems with sympathy  . Library  should not be a law enforcement  or business  place .
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for sharing your concerns; we are very sorry to hear that you have not had a good experience. We always welcome suggestions from patrons for titles that they would like us to add to our collection.  Thankfully we are part of the SCLENDS consortium, so there a wide variety of titles that patrons can choose from and place on hold for pick up at the Fort Mill Public Library, often within a few days. It is true that there is often a significant wait time for new bestsellers due to the financial impossibility of purchasing enough copies to satisfy public demand; this is a common challenge for public libraries. If you have not spoken to the branch manager about the book that you are sure you returned but are being required to pay for, please do so. We do have a procedure in place for those types of situations.  We hope to see you again soon.

I’m glad the “library” is there. However, library is probably not the most accurate way of describing this place. I would consider it a media center with a focus on lending books. This place is so loud. It is very difficult to study here. The staff talks at full volume with patrons. Patrons and staff laugh loudly.  Behind the circulation desk cabinets, and drawers are being slammed. There is no whispering or shushing, to create a quiet environment. It is really hard to study or do homework because of all the distractions. I wish there was a place to go for quiet studying. I do appreciate the access to books. Ordering books is easy online and to pick up.

Every time I go there, the staff (the older lady with the salt and pepper hair especially) at the front desk are rude.  Today was the last straw because I got barked at for just asking a simple question about the computers.  I won’t be back.
It is amazing so quiet

Not a very conducive place to go study. As a college student I wanted to go there to study over break, but the staff is very distracting as well as the little kids coming in to play.
There’s no isolated place for individual study, and only a couple of tables in which you can be easily distracted by people walking in or the staff chatting with each other.
Also the library is open at some pretty inconvenient hours, only during office hours. Real students study early mornings or late nights, I have no idea why they don’t extend hours for these times. This library is not college student friendly, it might as well be a Barnes and Noble without the coffee place. It needs some serious upgrades for it to be a good library. And it’s a shame because this is walking distance from my house.
It's close to everything. Has computers and printers that you v can use. Good selection of books and other media.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the review Jeff. Please feel free to let us know what we could do to get that last star.

reviews_data.review_text: It was o.k. Not enough time to do what I had planned.  😔
Books.
Excellent staff and great collection of books.

Nice library.  The staff is very friendly and capable.  While the library is on the small side it is a part of the SC Lends program letting you get books from a lot of the other SC member libraries delivered here which really opens up what is available.  I would also like to see an improvement to the hours - open later during the week and maybe even some Sunday hours.
It's Thursday not Friday and they are closed at 7pm, it seems unreasonably early to close at 7pm on a work/school day.
I was looking for books.  They have those, and lots of them.  Nice and friendly staff.
The staff is really helpful and friendly!

I love this library for myself and for my kids. It's in the heart of a residential area where families make up the majority of the demographic so it's not surprising to see young children learning to read and appreciate books with their parents. The selection here is based more on quality than quantity and when I can't find something it's very easy to request from another location. Very helpful and friendly staff, wheelchair friendly entrances, and clean. Thank you to our librarians who make it so pleasant!

As a college student trying to study here during break, this is not a good place. They staff is noisy and the people talk a lot with their kids. There is no quiet space dedicated to productive studying. There are only a few tables too.

I mean it is beautiful and gorgeous. But completely unfunctional for students looking to do work. I mean how do you expect the youth to get good grades if you don't provide us with adequate facilities to do the ridiculous amount of coursework we're supposed to accomplish? Typical old people not having a good perspective.

And it's not even open during the hours that students study. SMH.

This is classic old people not understanding what high schoolers/undergraduates face. "Let's open a library that only helps the elderly and the preschoolers." Cmon society. Stop it.
Nice and convenient one. My kids love to spend time there! Books n DVD collection may not be huge but you can request them from other locations.
Location is so convenient. Library is always clean and stocked. Everyone is so friendly and they have a lot of things for little ones.
Everyone is friendly. I can reserve my books ahead of time. I just wish there were more books.

This library is not college student friendly, it might as well be a Barnes and Noble without the coffee place. It needs some serious upgrades for it to be a good library. And it’s a shame because this is walking distance from my house.
It's close to everything. Has computers and printers that you v can use. Good selection of books and other media.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the review Jeff. Please feel free to let us know what we could do to get that last star.

reviews_data.review_text: It was o.k. Not enough time to do what I had planned.  😔
Books.
Excellent staff and great collection of books.

Nice library.  The staff is very friendly and capable.  While the library is on the small side it is a part of the SC Lends program letting you get books from a lot of the other SC member libraries delivered here which really opens up what is available.  I would also like to see an improvement to the hours - open later during the week and maybe even some Sunday hours.
It's Thursday not Friday and they are closed at 7pm, it seems unreasonably early to close at 7pm on a work/school day.
I was looking for books.  They have those, and lots of them.  Nice and friendly staff.
The staff is really helpful and friendly!

I love this library for myself and for my kids. It's in the heart of a residential area where families make up the majority of the demographic so it's not surprising to see young children learning to read and appreciate books with their parents. The selection here is based more on quality than quantity and when I can't find something it's very easy to request from another location. Very helpful and friendly staff, wheelchair friendly entrances, and clean. Thank you to our librarians who make it so pleasant!

As a college student trying to study here during break, this is not a good place. They staff is noisy and the people talk a lot with their kids. There is no quiet space dedicated to productive studying. There are only a few tables too.

I mean it is beautiful and gorgeous. But completely unfunctional for students looking to do work. I mean how do you expect the youth to get good grades if you don't provide us with adequate facilities to do the ridiculous amount of coursework we're supposed to accomplish? Typical old people not having a good perspective.

And it's not even open during the hours that students study. SMH.

This is classic old people not understanding what high schoolers/undergraduates face. "Let's open a library that only helps the elderly and the preschoolers." Cmon society. Stop it.
Nice and convenient one. My kids love to spend time there! Books n DVD collection may not be huge but you can request them from other locations.
Location is so convenient. Library is always clean and stocked. Everyone is so friendly and they have a lot of things for little ones.
Everyone is friendly. I can reserve my books ahead of time. I just wish there were more books.
